PRoject DEscription
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
During my time in Minnesota, I was working on a project to detect 1st order phase transforming superconductors.
Currently it is believed that all superconductors achieve superconductivity via a 2nd orer phase transition.
It is generally believed that this is universally true, despite some experimental predictions suggesting the latter.
We never found a smoking gun evidence suggesting that there can be a 1st order phase transforming superconductor.
We were analyzing all types of experimental data to see if we could explain them with a first order phase transition, but not
"easily" explainable using 2nd order phase transition ideas.

We had constructed a few thermodynamic model for superocnductors undergoing a first order phase transition and describing
some experimentally available data. Unfortunately, when we used the model to make some predictions for superconducting temperature
for thin films, the experiments didnt match reality. We lacked a smoking gun. A proof of a theory is in its ability to make better
predictions that the already existing properties.

Analyzing papers after paper of superconducting data to get some insight into what could be symptoms of a first order
phase transition was a never ending battle. So instead I decided to use GPT technology. 

I tried building a simple RAG agent to analyze pdf's, but i wasnt satisfied with the performance. Thus i decided to get my hands dirty and
work with a transformer.


